p: Before T H Cann Justice of the Peace.
To the Sheriff or any Constable of said County, Greeting:

Whereas, J H Wooley has this day complained in writing, under oath, to the undersigned, one of the Justices of the Peace in and for said County, that on the 10 day of November 1882 at at Seattle in said County Defendants did the case of a have kept for opium smoking set forth on part for the purpose of smoking
Therefore, in the name of the United States you are commanded forthwith to apprehend the said Deft, Chin Chung and bring him before me, to be dealt with according to law.
Given under my hand this 11 day of Nov 1882
